*sylpheed-claws-0.8.5 (09 Oct 2002)

  12 Oct 2002; Bruce A. Locke <blocke@shivan.org> sylpheed-claws-0.8.5.ebuild:
  Ebuild now installs README files, etc.

  09 Oct 2002; Brad Cowan <bcowan@gentoo.org> sylpheed-claws-0.8.5.ebuild,
  files/digest-sylpheed-claws-0.8.5 :
  
  Version bump with minor bugfixes.

*sylpheed-claws-0.8.3 (24 Sep 2002)
  
  24 Sep 2002; Seemant Kulleen <seemant@gentoo.org>
  sylpheed-claws-0.8.3.ebuild files/digest-sylpheed-claws-0.8.3 :

  Version bump which fixes more memory leaks and sorts out the aspell issue.
  Thanks to: moixa@gmx.ch (Tobias Sager) in bug #8218 and
  bradlyatc@cowancomputers.com (Brad Cowan) in bug #8249.

*sylpheed-claws-0.8.2 (28 Aug 2002)

  6 Sep 2002; Owen Stampflee <owen@gentoo.org> :
  Added PPC to KEYWORDS.

  28 Aug 2002; Seemant Kulleen <seemant@gentoo.org>
  sylpheed-claws-0.8.2.ebuild files/digest-sylpheed-claws-0.8.2 :

  Version bump which fixes many memory leaks.  The dillo and aspell patches
  are still applied on this release as well.  Thanks to: hanno@gmx.de (Hanno
  Boeck) in bug #7166

*sylpheed-claws-0.8.1-r1 (17 Aug 2002)

  17 Aug 2002; Seemant Kulleen <seemant@gentoo.org>
  sylpheed-claws-0.8.1-r1.ebuild files/digest-sylpheed-claws-0.8.1-r1 :

  Jared Hudson (jhhudso@gentoo.org) fixed up the
  embeddable-dillo-within-sylpheed patch from
  http://melvin.hadasht.free.fr/home/dillo/sylpheed/ so that it actually
  works now.  In order to see HTML in e-mails, emerge sylpheed-claws with
  the "gtkhtml" USE flag enabled.  Also, this release has a patch by me to
  make it work with aspell-0.50*

